comment: Vucevic (ORL) sets the screen on Crowder (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Johnson (BOS) sets the screen on Payton (ORL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Payton (ORL) legally contests Thomas' (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Fournier (ORL) sets the screen on Horford (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Gordon (ORL) jumps from point A to point B into the body of Horford (BOS) and the contact affects his shot attempt.
Vucevic (ORL) makes marginal contact with Crowder (BOS) following the screen.
Vucevic (ORL) and Johnson (BOS) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Gordon (ORL) makes incidental contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Gordon (ORL) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) legally contests Ross' (ORL) jump shot attempt.
Fournier (ORL) legally contests Thomas' (BOS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Vucevic (ORL) and Smart (BOS) make incidental contact with one another off ball.
Johnson (BOS) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Payton (ORL) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
